    "description": "Are you a skilled Consultant Physician looking for your next big career move? Sankara Nethralaya Consulting Pvt Ltd in Ranchi offers you the perfect platform to grow professionally and personally.\n\nAbout Sankara Nethralaya Consulting Pvt Ltd:\nSankara Nethralaya Consulting Pvt Ltd is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Ranchi, Jharkhand, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Sankara Nethralaya Consulting Pvt Ltd!",
